{"name":"Exploding arrow","type":"artifact","img":"systems/cyphersystem/icons/items/artifact.svg","system":{"version":2,"description":"<p><strong>Level:</strong> 1d6</p>\n<p><strong>Form:</strong> Arrow with runes carved on the shaft and head</p>\n<p><strong>Effect:</strong> The arrow explodes when it strikes something, inflicting its level in damage to all within immediate range. Roll [[/r d100]] to determine the type of damage.</p>\n<table style=\"height: 85px; width: 100%; border-width: 1px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 15%;\"><col style=\"width: 85%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; border-width: 1px; padding: 4px; text-align: center;\">01&ndash;20</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; border-width: 1px; padding: 4px;\">Acid</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; border-width: 1px; padding: 4px; text-align: center;\">21&ndash;40</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; border-width: 1px; padding: 4px;\">Electricity</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; border-width: 1px; padding: 4px; text-align: center;\">41&ndash;60</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; border-width: 1px; padding: 4px;\">Cold</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; border-width: 1px; padding: 4px; text-align: center;\">61&ndash;90</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; border-width: 1px; padding: 4px;\">Fire</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; border-width: 1px; padding: 4px; text-align: center;\">91&ndash;00</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; border-width: 1px; padding: 4px;\">Necromantic (harms only flesh)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><strong>Depletion:</strong> Automatic</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>One advantage of an exploding arrow over a detonation cypher is that the arrow doesn&rsquo;t count toward your cypher limit.</p>\n<p>An exploding arrow can instead be a crossbow bolt, sling stone, or other thrown weapon or projectile.</p>\n</b